# Movie Finder — qdrant-explorer MCP Cursor Rules

This file is a legacy fallback. Cursor loads the richer MDC rules from `.cursor/rules/` automatically.

If your IDE supports MDC rules, the following files apply:
- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always active (MCP server context, exposed tools)
- `.cursor/rules/python.mdc` — activates on `**/*.py`
- `.cursor/rules/architect.mdc` — activates when designing new MCP tools
- `.cursor/rules/developer.mdc` — activates when implementing issues

---

## Quick reference

**Repo:** `aharbii/movie-finder-mcp-qdrant` · Primary context: `CLAUDE.md`

**Non-negotiables:**
- `mypy --strict` must pass — no `type: ignore` without explanatory comment
- No bare `except:` — catch specific types
- No `print()` — use logging
- Must run via `uv run` (stdio) — no runtime installation required
- Dependencies isolated in local `uv.lock` — never pollute production workspace
- Conventional Commits: `feat(mcp): summary`
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR
